reviews.text: I use to frequent this store until the older Indian male that runs the store began charging for each topping ( not meat but hot peppers) that I requested more of. That is not how any other subway restaurant that I have been to does it. Subway is no longer worth the money, Wawa is taking over with their yummy subs and better prices.

Let me in and did NOT make me a sandwich. They said the store is closed. I would NOT have said anything BUT they were making sandwiches for 2 other people as I was walking in. Common courtesy, if you have your sign ON and you do not have your door locked AND you are making others sandwiches you should have made me a sandwich as "good customer service"...NEVER coming to this Subway again....Bye Felicia...

I will NEVER again visit this place.  Today there was some young kid there who couldn't understand English.  Also, he seemed more focused on what he was preparing for himself in the microwave that he only half-listened to my questions.  This is very poor service and it should be mentioned.

I want to share my experience in this place, I spent Friday night buying two subways but the manager who was on the line super bad customer service, he was talking on his headphones and when I was asking him for the ingredients of my order he just put to laugh and wonder again what I wanted in my sandwich, but the laugh was with the person who was talking on the phone. And the same thing happened with another client who was behind me. Bad experience I do not recommend coming at night......
FRESH INGREDIENTS AND VERY FRIENDLY ESTABLISHMENT.

I came here for the first time for dinner a few nights ago. Customer service was fantastic. The young man at the counter was very helpful when I told him it was my first time there.  I had the 10 boneless wings, half sweet Thai chili/ medium  jerk flavors and an order of regular fries. The sweet Thai chili wings were good. I was not impressed with the medium jerk wings. The taste was just not a good jerk taste to me, so I don't recommend that flavor.  A picture of the jerk wings is attached. Sorry for not including pics of the other food - I ate it too fast! The fries were fine, regular fries, could of used a little salt, but they give you a nice amount. The packaging was great (I did take out). I like the containers that they use. I would try them again, but maybe next time I would go with the sweet potato fries and no jerk flavor wings.

Love the flavors of wings from here! The owner is so kind and knows his menu well. Helped us choose exactly what we needed and everything is SO delicious. Our kids loved the mac and cheese. Will definitely be back 🙂

The boneless chicken is sooo tender!!! For a typical chicken wing spot, they are impressive. Other places use chicken from (seems like) the same supplier or use store-bought. You can SEE and TASTE the difference here. They are heavy on the salt so beware of that.

Atomic Wings was a very good quick bite. It has a sports theme throughout and plenty of TVs to watch from. The menu screens were off when I went so I had to dig around a little to figure out what to order. There were specials posted throughout on printed signs but it was almost like a scavenger hunt. Once I got the paper menu off of a table then we were able to look at the full menu. The prices were reasonable and the portions were generous. I was pretty nervous about how well it was going to taste but would say it’s on par with the expectations of quick bite restaurant. The fries and empanadas could be a bit better but yhe wing options were vast and delicious. The cashier was nice enough to let us sample some prior to ordering. I would definitely eat there again but I wouldn’t go out my way for it.

Great halal options and the most delicious wings off campus. I order from here all the time and I'm a hot wing connoisseur so i really value a good, delicious wing. Must be juicy and crispy and that's exactly what they are ... oh and the waffle fries are to die for.

This is by far the best sushi in the greater College Park, Hyattsville, Silver Spring area.  The place is not fancy but don't let that fool you. The sushi is fresh and delicious. Service is fast and friendly.  Due to covid it is take out only.  They have all the appropriate measures in place to make them and you safe.

Can you all please stop basing your reviews off of door dash, uber eats and delivery services. That's not fair to the business or the employees there. They work with you so well when you're there and if something is off, it may have been the app. If you were charged more than in person, it is solely on the app. Not them. Delivery services have their own prices and ALWAYS up the prices. That is why I dont use delivery apps. So everyone should ignore reviews based on price differences on the apps. The apps also limit special orders. As in "you cannot get things special ordered on apps requested." Please keep that in mind before making reviews.

I was a regular here. I'd recommend this place to anyone who loves hibachi! They're always kind and always get my order just right! Try the yum yum sauce with your hibachi meal. It's so good.  Remember to tip! They deserve it!

I am highly disappointed in this place today this is the first time that they get an order wrong through door dash my boyfriend always orders from here and today he decided to order some for me and his baby to eat and literally they got the order wrong and they didn’t even decide to double check because I ordered chicken teriyaki with fried rice and vegetables with shrimp and I didn’t even get that today and they really messed up his order and wasted his money

Really bummed out that my "salad with ginger dressing" turned out to be 2 tomato slices iceberg Lettuce and ranch,  like it was taken out of someone's sub or something,  instead of the typical ginger dressing salad one would expect from a Japanese restaurant

First of all, I’d like to say that I read all the reviews on this place before coming and was still a bit hesitant as to whether or not this would be a great place for sushi. And let me tell you, after ordering takeout from this place, I cannot stress how delicious the sushi is. It’s fresh and tastes so good! My favorite was the shrimp tempura roll, absolutely to die for. Will definitely be coming here again soon!!
Great atmosphere. Mr. Greg was very friendly and such a great host. Kay was our bartender she was WONDERFUL her drinks were AMAZING. I've been recommending this place everyday since I went

Strong drinks, amazing food and great service. Steak and cheese egg rolls...bomb! Onion rings w/ spicy ranch...bomb! Friend wings...bomb! Fish Sandwich....bomb! Bartender was sweet and attentive. Played music, but was very empty. It was a random Tuesday, so it wasn't crowded at all. If you are looking for somewhere to go to mingle, this isn't it. I heard it was busy on Thursday's for karaoke, but I'm not sure.

Karokee got the party started for sure. The service was great (cute bartender-tasty drinks-respectful security-VERY accommodating). Food was okay-just okay. You have to order through their app and gratuity is automatically included. I'd return for happy hour or another karokee night.

Black,family owned. We sat at the bar, the bartender was very pleasant and welcoming for our first time there. I didn't like that my husband and I couldn't order with the bartender, we had to go thru their QR code. There were only 7 people at the bar including us two. But nevertheless the food was hot and came out quick. We ordered chx tenders and wings. Drinks were good and food was good. I will be back I want to see this place when it's packed and busy.

Food Made with Love, BOB, Kay the bartender energy and drinks are beyond measure, the whole entire staff is awesome.  TV clarity looks so live.  Greet for business meetings as well.  Love it.  Hidden Gemstone.

Totally remodeled and looks great. Ample parking directly in front. Great atmosphere.  Awesome cooked food selections . Very pleasant staff. Nice bar area with big screen flats. Has a birthday celebration 🎂 🎈 🎉

This place is Nostalgic.
You can order To-Go or Dine-In w/ friends.

I ordered mines To-Go and when I got home I was soooooo delighted. The food was fresh, tasted delicious and was flavorful. The fish literally melted in my mouth.

I’m now addicted.

When in Maryland GO-HERE!

So many people recommended this place to us. We decided to go visit since friends and family were visiting. There is a large menu and several drink items to chose from. The restaurant has most of the side items already prepared and displayed like buffet style for you to see. They sell cakes and other desserts too. The food was good. The shrimp was pre-breaded and not fresh caught shrimp. The tilapia and catfish were good. Most of the our friends liked the food and would go back again

Our first time here and I feel Iike I just had a meal down south ! Talk about delicious food ! And the music is 😆 let’s just say my momma would love it here .. they have also dine in, take out, door dash delivery and a cute bar with TVs above 👍🏼👍🏼

Absolutely awesome atmosphere.  We has a small birthday 🎂 🥳 party in a prerecorded section of the restaurant.  Everyone could see tge tV to watch the Sunday NFL games. The staff was courteous and friendly.

I  usually patronize this business today i went there to cash a 10.00 lottery ticket the clerk was by himself he was busy going back in forth another customer who i know was in line to cash  a ticket also for 10.00 we both had just left 7-11 because their machine was down. He gave him his 10.00 ,  I asked were is my 10.00 he said I didn't give him the ticket, I asked him to look around maybe it failed down, there was a ticket on the counter in the other man who saw me put the ticket on the counter starting looking around the back in grabbed some ticket  from behind the counter. I called to  speak to the manager tolook at the camera  he said will be in tomorrow. I will speak with the manager tomorrow.  If you make  a mistake or you are unsure you need to own up to it?
I'm annoyed because he isn't taking responsibility for his actions. If this isn't resolved I will not patronize this business.

The prices here are okay, better with the Fuel Rewards card. Occasionally this place will fill up with cars (Thursdays!) and you have to wait a few minutes for a spot to open up or an idle car to move out of the way. The pumps normally provide receipts so you don't have to go inside. And on the whole the windshield squeegees are kept in working order.

Cashier refused to give me more than $2 in change for the air machine. After using $1.50 in the machine, I had filled 2 tires and managed to make one go flat. The clerk said there is a $2 quarter limit and refused to give me any more quarters. If you are going to try to inflate your tires or vacuum your car, make sure you bring your own quarters.
Customer Service is good but the Prices are awfully expensive!!!
This was the first place I've experienced cashier stealing money from customers, count your money always just like that 7-Eleven Riverdale, but this was before the pandemic

Very slow fixing your order. I had to remind them what I ordered. It seems like they only cared about the drive thru. To many people working to be that slow. The frozen drinks taste pretty good but very runny.
Unsanitary, I saw bread on floor and worker picking it up with the glove. Then doing more orders without changing the dirty glove. Mess up people order.

I arrived at 6:00 am the drive thru was closed until 6:30 am. Please change you google schedule . I thought this was suppose to be open since 5 am. By the time you open about 10 -15  potential costumers pass your drive thru.
Inside store service closed. Drive through only. Man in wheelchair ordering from drive through (not inside a vehicle) took 10-15 minutes to resolve his order so line for days.
I went later in the day so mornings may be better but the donuts were a little stale and the selection a little sad. I may give them another chance but was not impressed

I came in there and went in and asked for the rest room and they said to go to dollar store because the one there was out of service. When I came back there was someone in front of me giving order growing visa I’ll frustrated because the person making sandwich whats yelling and having loud convo and customer had to keep treating herself. She walked out because he kept yelling on phone and having her repeat herself. He was moving exceptionally slow. After she walked out and told him why she was leaving, I was surprised to see him doing the same with me. He had me repeat every part of the order and I asked him to “get off the phone while I made my order” but he was still talking. So I left too. He didn’t even notice I started recording before I left too. The video is attached. Management needs tk do something about this guy.

I'm the only customer in the store and no one seems like they wanted to wait on me. Then some guy walks in and they immediately served him. I said "I'm standing here to order way before this guy walked in", and they're saying he got a online order. Poor service and rudeness at its highest.  Never go to this store. Nasty employees with terrible attitude. Worse service here with over priced food

DO NOT ORDER FROM THIS SUBWAY

Twice this week I've tried to order from the subway website and the website goes through with the order and then when doordash gets there the order gets canceled.

Both times my text message says to call the restaurant and both times I got the worst attitude from a man who kept telling me to call doordash. Every time I told him I ordered it from Subway and not doordash he kept saying to call doordash. Subway took the money from my cars and this restaurant doesn't want anything to do with it.

There's a Jerry's next door I'm just going to start ordering from them. At least they care about their customers

Janky. Rude. Unprofessional. I put it in online order for dinner for my family, the order went through money was taken out of my account I go to pick up my food and before I get to go in someone from the store calls my cell phone telling me to bring my ID and card. Huh? To pick up some sandwiches? That I already ordered online and was charged for? He kept trying to bring up some policy that they have but it all sounded janky to me then started to yell at me over the phone and hung up on me next thing a manager calls me from a whole different phone number because he wasn't even in the store and try to explain the same janky policy that they claim that they have now which I have never ever heard of especially ordering online food as I have also ordered from Subway online before the different location never had this issue. After going back and forth told them to cancel the order the manager continues to text my phone I don't know what type of scamming janky stuff these people are on but avoid this Subway if you can there are plenty other better locations near these guys are horrible I would never step foot in this raggedy establishment.
He is make good sub,he doing good work

I never been so annoyed in my life.
I showed the cashier the deep dishes and told him this looks very poorly made and it's  misshapen. He told me 'That's how it's suppose to look " This will definitely be my last time attending this location..

The pizza at this location has been excessively oily to the point that it feels like the pizza is soaking wet.  Heating up the  pizza in the microwave  makes the sogginess worst.  In order to make the pizza a little firm, I have to place the pizza in the oven for about 15 minutes.  I don't like soggy pizza.
If I can give 0 stars I would! Rude workers, Ghetto handwritten signs in lobby (improper grammar) This place is ran by kids! DO BETTER LITTLE CAESARS

Today is Friday October 28th 2022 3:15pm, I never seen a terrible customer service in my life, what to get a pizza, cashier talking at the phone with the ear phone, try to explain to her about the credit card machine wasn't working and never responded, I have to walk away and go somewhere else to get pizza for my little boy, this place it just to be a nice customer service, but not any more,  I never will come back to this place
My kids are split between the stuffed crust and deep dish. I love the  Pizza Portal and the price.

Whenever we have family visiting from the Midwest they want to visit this burger chain. They are always well pleased. Today was the same. One person got a triple Buford and he enjoyed thoroughly. Another ordered a burger with bacon and she enjoyed it as well. One of the teen wagers ordered a “brookie” which is a combination of a cookie and brownie. The fries and seasoning were perfect.

This location really had me waiting at the window for about 20+ minutes with 0 acknowledgement. I was just picking up a doordash order. It was busy when I first got there but after about 5 minutes or so, it died down. And the order that I was waiting for was sitting right on the counter! But everyone was too busy talking to each other and checking their phones.

Came to this location for a late night meal, being they didn't close until 4 am. We got to the drive thru at 3:25 am and a lady start to take our order then all of a sudden went quiet. Thinking the intercom broke, we drove up to the window,  where the same lady was seen mouthing "we're closed". I then got out the car to get clarification, because why would you start taking our order then disappear. She acted like she didnt see me and another gentleman standing outside so I tapped the window. She came to the window but did not open it, but again she mouthed "we're closed", in which i replied, "but you start taking our order". Then she says, through the window, "we aint got no more food". I then walk off. The whole experience was ridiculous and I was very disappointed.
This company need to get its act together. The wait at the restaurant is on another level. I waited 1 hours for a meal, shhhhh.
Ask for light salt on the fries if you're sensitive because they go heavy on it. The service was good and the burger tasty.

I use to love Sammy's alot. I patronized them for YEARS. The son is very rude! I miss their daughter, the mother knows me. When I ask for everything as well as additional on my sandwiches,  the don't comply. I don't know what's going on with them. They really use to be my go too....and I gmfind my heading to CENTURY. TURN AROUND Sammy's.
Worst Chinese food I’ve ever tried. The General Taos chicken was like meatless rubber.

I haven't been to this place in years. At one point when I ordered from them I found mealworm..at least 12 or 13 of them inside of one of the dishes that was to contain three meats. I had this verified by Google pictures and also by a good friend who happens to know exactly what it looks like as her brother loves it. Never went there again. And never will! When I took the dish in to get my money back they said it was baby lobster! No way in hell that was baby lobster. I hope they discontinued this practice, but just the thought of it, turns me off completely from this place.

Ordered from here yesterday before the snow started. I have multiple children so my order was over $50. Got it home and went to eat it, and it was HORRIBLE!!! Tasted and smelled like the grease they cooked some of the food in was a month old VERY NASTY!!! By the time we had sat down to eat, it had already started snowing. So we had to keep the food that was fine and throw the bad food in the trash. WASTE OF MONEY!!! Won't eat there any longer or recommend this place.
This is the worst place ever, just take a look what i get last time, what is this food??? it was just a waste of money, nobody wanted to eat that, this came from that place direct to my trash

My first time visiting was yesterday. I read the previous reviews and they did NOT lie. The food was GREAT! I had the Nachos which were only $10.00! They were fresh, portioned perfectly, and very tasty. The customer service was just as good. I’m definitely returning here. 10/10!
Beautiful place and very attentive people, excellent. 😎
Too slow. Long wait . If you go here order food ahead of time. If you go in hungry you will starve.
Enjoyed the  family feel  a great neighborhood  spot to get away the food is good and you get your money worth

Great atmosphere!! Official size pool tables which is cool too see and the best part is the authentic Salvadorian food!! They have different events and concerts which varies from time to time.  Loves the service from the owner (who is always there) Yolanda it’s great to know that the owner is also the cook!
Any one craving local Cameroonian and African dishes...this is your must-go restaurant. The menu is attached for your quick reference. Wait time was okay...there is enough parking.
I ordered Egusi soup and received a big tray of rice for $20 on Uber eats. Did not receive a refund.

THEY SENT US SPOILED EGUSI PUDDING!!
They don’t value Uber eats customers.
We have been ordering delivery several times a week. You never know if the soya will be days old or if the plantain will be dried out.
We kept ordering because we like the food… when made fresh.
Today was horrible , dried out bitter soya and rotten egusi.
My husband and I went running to the bathroom to spit it out. Over $100 in food and we have to throw it out.
When we called to complain their response was “ sorry ask Uber for your money back”.
My advice is eat in the restaurant , don’t deliver .

These people were so rude to me and my friend. I’m AA and he is from Sierra Leone. I love music and good food and we heard the vibes were good so we gave it a try. It was like everything my friend asked for the women behind the bar gave him attitude. They were so disrespectful to him.

No options for mild/no spicy foods. I gave this place 2 stars only because it’s a beautiful place, the DJ was good, and the security guard (w/dreads) was very nice. Other than that I would not recommend this place .

In my years of being a local guide. I can say this is probably the first time I did not recommend a restaurant. Those women were so disrespectful.

I am at Md Live Kitchen.  I ordered 1 slice  of pizza.  Took 40 minutes to get service after asking what's going on. Something that should have taken 5 minutes to get since it was already in the window.  I ask for the manager all he said was I'm sorry. But I come here all the time and always get treated like trash. Never again with the service.  Get people that care about customer service instead of eating everything you serve and eating it all like the manager. He happy because he eating all the food. Came out to serve me chewing smh

So I put my order in 15 minutes before I even arrived. I waited in the pick up order line as there was another person who was in front of me. They were there to pick up, gave the name and their food was not ready. None of the pick up food was ready. There were about 4 of us standing there while the young man prepared her order which he moved so slow it took him about 15 minutes to do. Her order was not big at all. After he finished that, as two other people were already ringing on the registers just as slowly as him, he walked away from the pick up line and hopped on the Register. We were all stunned that he just blatantly disrespected us like that. A customer behind me said she was about to say something after they finished with the walk in orders still being rung out. An additional 5 minutes later...so I've been in this store now for almost 25 minutes still waiting on a pick up order, a woman walked up with an attitude, spiky ponytail with no hair net and asked was I picking up, I said yes of course. She took an additional 10 minutes to prepare my order. Pick up order customers stood frustrated but all agreed, there's a reason why they have so much security in there. The way they disrespect customers and ignore them, I'm sure some people have gone off in there. Be nice to your customers. Don't ignore them. If you hate your job, quit. There's so many jobs hiring with better environments. Overall, I will never return to this location again. I wouldn't advise anyone else do so either. Almost 40 minutes for a pickup order with a full house of slow motion employees.

I think her name is Gloria. She was so amazing. My bag. Not the food slipped out her hand. Do u know she re made the order. An didn't have to. That is service you just don't see anymore in the fast food industry. Good job! 😊

When I came in, there two women working at the counter.  One was flirting with the security guard while the other lady , Ms Edna, was serving one person with a couple waiting to order and me being the third person. After the flirtatious lady,  which I think was the manager with long ponytail locks, finished with the guard,  she walked back to her office like there were no customers in line, and leave Ms Edna by her self to serve the rest of the customers. This happened 12/3 @ 10:37pm.

I placed an online order and still had to wait for my food for an additional 15mins along with other folks waiting for the online orders they placed as well.
Wouldn't recommend this location.
The employees (the woman) here are just mad at the world.
Food was good but service terrible.

Just creepy. Between the two security guards with only one customer in the restaurant and them not having anything else to do but stop having a personal conversation to stand behind and stare at customers. The three employees literally just standing around with their hand on the wall knowing they needed to cleanup. My food was overcooked. It was just a weird experience. I was too uncomfortable to go back.

Good food, menu is loaded with options.
One of the more clean and better quality carry out around.
This will be my new favorite go to Chinese food place.
Above average carry out in my opinion.
Not the best ambiance inside, but you know it’s a carry out what you expect.
Lunch menu is cheapppp too haven’t tried yet but their portion is pretty decent dinner wise.
The Lunch Special Is Very Good! I Love The Orange Chicken And Fries And Rice.I Go Here Everytime With My Mom
This is the best carry out I’ve had in years. Probably the best! The wings and shrimp fried rice were amazing.
Just came here for the 1st time and really enjoyed our meal. The chicken I got was great I didn't notice any grizle on the chicken. We will definitely come back again.
I have no complaints their food is excellent the staff is very nice and friendly. I recommend New Century for great food.
Got an order of pupusas and they were delicious, friendly staff and good service

The food its bomb but customer  service its wack no education  on waiting for the customer waitress are inpatient  and if you want to change things from your plate for example t bone steaks comes with broccoli  want to change it for rice or any other side you could think off the waitress told me they werent able to change it not even if customer its asking I think we pay got the right to ask food to make some changes without a problem maybe  I could be wrong
Staff is friendly. Food is served fresh. Love the Pupusas. A nice place to go with family. Covid 19 safety measures are bein taken.
Good food, pupusas are delicious, the bartender is friendly and has excellent customer service

I had dinner there with a friend. We ordered pupusas. The atmosphere was nice, the food delicious, and the horchata traditional.

The only reason I did not give it 5 stars was because we tried 3 booths before we found one with a table that did not rock.

I haven't been here in forever. I ordered 4pcs of wings and a large shrimp with broccoli. Absolutely delicious. I also got a Modelo beer.

Came here today 4/12/22 since it's been a while when they shut down due to COVID-19. Still got yummy 😋 food. Nice to return to

Stopped by there for some fries and vegetable fried rice, not the best experience at all.
Got home to dig in, it wasn't looking the greatest and no taste. The fries were worse, half cooked to raw, had to finish backing them in the oven to get them done - it didn't matter, even with salt on them, the fries just taste bad. 🤢 My first and last time there! 😤😡🤬

Food was horrible, I ordered Kung Pao Chicken and it didn’t have any taste nor was it spicy as I asked for Extra Hot. There were no peppers or onions only carrots and celery. Garbage and wouldn’t recommend 🤮🤢
A friend referred us to this spot after we had a bad experience with another carryout. I love it! Their steak cheese eggrolls are bomb and their fried wings never disappoint.
It gets the job done... Once you get past the wife's somewhat snarky attitude you'll find the food is halfway decent and worth coming back for.
